title: Middlesbrough 3 - 2 Oxford United
text:
Middlesbrough's Cristhian Stuani celebrates scoring his side's third goal of the game with team mate Middlesbrough's Gaston Ramirez during the Emirates FA Cup, Fifth Round match at the Riverside Stadium, Middlesbrough. Credit: PA Middlesbrough are into the FA Cup quarter-finals after fending off League One Oxford United at the Riverside.
At half-time the Boro were 2-0 up against Oxford United. But two goals a minute apart meant the score was leveled 2-2.
Christian Stuani scored in the final few minutes bringing the score to Middlesbrough 3, Oxford United 2.
Middlesbrough will find out their quarter-final opponents in Sunday's draw which takes place at 6.30pm on the BBC.
Last updated Sat 18 Feb 2017 Middlesbrough
